  175                     ; A little introduction to the boot sequence:
  176                     ;
  177                     ; A HuCard has its origin at bank 0, and is mapped at $E000
  178                     ; It needs to grab the interrupt vectors at $FFF6 and implement
  179                     ; implement handlers for them
  180                     ;
  181                     ; A CDROM will load at bank $80 ($68 for SCD), and the initial
  182                     ; loader will be mapped at $4000.  The current MagicKit sequence
  183                     ; also maps $C000 to this same bank.  However, the initial boot
  184                     ; sequence will execute at $4070, proceeding to load additional
  185                     ; code and data, and then jump to a post-boot section called
  186                     ; 'init_go'.  This is the point at which the loader explicitly
  187                     ; relinquishes the $4000 segment.  It should be noted that there
  188                     ; are library subroutines loaded as part of this initial segment,
  189                     ; and those routines are located in the $C000 range as well.
  190                     ;
  191                     ; Sectors are loaded, up to and including the first "DATA_BANK",
  192                     ; where the overlay array is stored - so that the CDROM error
  193                     ; overlay can be located and executed in the event of a CDROM
  194                     ; system version mismatch (ie. playing SCD games on CDROM)
  195                     ;
  196                     ; A second entry point is defined for overlays that are not
  197                     ; being booted (ie. they are loaded and executed from another
  198                     ; overlay).  This entry point is at $4000, after the segments
  199                     ; have all found their natural loading spots (ie. segment $68
  200                     ; for Super CDROMs).  This entry point maps the necessary
  201                     ; segments and resets the stack, without clearing memory or
  202                     ; performing other setup chores, and then maps and executes
  203                     ; _main() to run the module.  The user has no choice regarding
  204                     ; this function, although he can pass values through the global
  205                     ; variables which main() can use to decide what to do next.
  206                     ;
  207                     ; An additional "Hook" area has now been defined at $4028,
  208                     ; which is used at initial load time, in case a SCD overlay
  209                     ; program is run on plain CDROM hardware, and the author
  210                     ; wishes to override the default text error message by
  211                     ; loading and executing a plain CDROM program instead
  212                     ;
